(See my earlier reel). An unforgettable moment in time. 🙏🙏 @charmossny @chateauversailles #marieantoinette #templeoflove #lepetitetrianon #QueensHamlet

Exploring the ruins of the 10th century Islamic palace-city Medina Azahara (the most significant archaeological site from the Islamic era in Córdoba, Spain besides the mosque).
The museum complex, beautifully done, was designed by esteemed architects Fuensanta Nieto and Enrique Sobejano, winning the Aga Khan Architecture Award in 2010. The excavation is currently stopped due to lack of funding and they say only 11% has been unearthed. #archeology #indagarespain
Córdoba’s massive Catholic cathedral, formerly a mosque, a UNESCO world heritage site. It’s size is seemingly endless with 740 marble columns! #theydontbuildthemliketheyusedto
#justlookup  #ceilings #Indagarespain

Visiting the Alhambra is a pure sensory overload of delights so I’ll post in several batches… the outside and gardens first... hard to believe it was abandoned and ignored for so many years. #fountains #runnells #islamicdecor #indagarespain #travelinspo #pageknox

In the Islamic tradition, the exterior of buildings were utterly plain with no elaboration or decoration which was the 180 degree opposite inside where every surface was completely covered in detailed geometric decoration and ornamentation. And then painted and gilded!! It boggles the mind to realize what they built centuries ago with the extraordinary craftsmanship and talent at hand. #islamicart #giftsfromGod #indagarespain #pageknox
The Alhambra at night… no words needed. #Alhambra #breathtakinglybeautiful #mustseeatnight #indagarespain #pageknox

Wonderful article in the New York Times today about “Barbie’s Dreamhouse”. I am often asked what inspired my career in design. Certainly growing up in paradise in Montecito with beautiful gardens, great architecture, and a lovely lifestyle was an inspiration. But, having a much older father, I was definitely not encouraged to have a career… I don’t recall that word ever uttered in our house!  But my parents always encouraged me in my creativity and artistic abilities. Flashback to Xmas of ‘64, when I wanted a new blue bike, I was given a Barbie Dreamhouse and while rather disappointed and not overly Barbie-crazed, I did play with it for hours and hours on end! Made of cardboard and cleverly unfolding, you could buy all the furniture and accessories to go with it, rearrange all the furniture over and over and play out your fantasies. What I particularly love about this @nytimes article is it points to the fact that it was Barbie’s house and not Ken’s. (Women couldn’t get a mortgage without a husband in those days!) Nor was there a kitchen in the first house, unlike other toys which were encouraging girls to be domestic happy homemakers. This dream house was simply encouraging a girl to have fun! She had a record player so she could dance, she had books so she could read, and her own TV! And invite Ken over when she felt like it - very independent! “The house has served as a subliminal, maybe even subversive, blueprint for children, especially girls. Barbie’s Dreamhouse was all her own — Ken was not on the deed.” And in the 70’s Helen Gurley Brown, of seductive Cosmo fame, told women to play tennis to meet men so Barbie had a tennis racket in her later Dreamhouses which have evolved considerably over the years.  So, I’ll credit my mother, while completely unaware, that Christmas gift in 1964 was undoubtedly an inspiration and a catalyst for me to spend my life, rearranging furniture, decorating homes, and building dream houses! Thanks, Mummy! 🙏🙏🌸🌸😘💞💞 #BarbiesDreamhouse #MontecitoGirl

Beautiful evening visiting the extraordinary Frank Lloyd Wright Auldbrass Plantation.  Thank you, Joel!  A modification of ”Old Brass,” the name given to the 4,000-acre tract of land on the banks of the Combahee River, the plantation is one of the largest and most complex residential projects Wright ever undertook. Wright’s vision—including a main house, guest house, cabins, caretaker’s residence, staff cabins, barn stables, aviary and pond with floating ‘dining barge’—manages to incorporate his characteristic pagoda-like spires, hexagonal motifs, and organic influences. Linked by esplanades, the collection of slender, one-story buildings feature exterior walls made of native cypress and set at an 80-degree angle to recall the slant of the oak trees that dot the property. Though Wright worked on the Auldbrass commission over a twenty-year period, only half of the planned buildings were realized before the death of both Wright and the client. The plantation had fallen into disrepair until it was bought by acclaimed Hollywood producer Joel Silver (Lethal Weapon, The Matrix, Die Hard) in 1986. With the help of the architect’s grandson, Eric Lloyd Wright, Auldbrass was meticulously restored and eventually completed. The cars were given to Frank Loyd Wright in 1940 by the Ford Motor Co as a promotion for the Lincoln Continental.  Wright insisted on his own custom interior and color. Hence the Cherokee red.  #franklloydwright @auldbrass #americanarchitecture

Every detail of the main house at Auldbrass Plantation was designed by Frank Lloyd Wright.  Hexagons to the nth degree! The kitchen, the floors, tables, lamps, rugs, etc., etc., etc.! It’s a rare and extraordinary compound of buildings with Wright’s focus on everything to be with the landscaoe at 80 degree angles like the slant of the trees. See previous post. Bravo, Joel Silver for the passion and self-admitted obsession it took to bring this dream to reality!! This makes The Matrix look easy!  @auldbrass #franklloydwright

When a friend calls on short notice to join her for a weekend in DC celebrating The Kennedy Center Honorees Billy Crystal, Renée Fleming, Sir Barry Gibb, Queen Latifah and Dionne Warwick… you change your plans and say YES!! What a wonderful weekend it was from lunch at the Kennedy Center to welcome the honorees - adorable Rita Moreno at our table - and the Secretary of State’s dinner in the beautiful  Benjamin Franklin State Dining Room - Secretary Blinken is such a good speaker - to the next day at the White House where the holiday decorations almost overshadow POTUS and FLOTUS and the honorees all together - Dazzling!! And then on to the Show at the fabulous Kennedy Center!  It was so moving, very personal tributes, brilliantly produced with star-studded surprises at every turn! I’m not easily starstruck but this was WOW! 🤩 Watch it on CBS on December 27th. #billycrystal #barrygibb #reneefleming #queenlatifah #dionnewarwick #justsayYES Thank you, dear friend Phyllis! #luckygirlthatIam! 🙏🙏♥️♥️
